stylometry: A regression equation determines the effect of a variable on the outcome. It is used for prediciting what will occur based on different predeterminations. For example, there are expected results of apartmenst rented based upon the number of adds placed. It will show an upward regression because of the strong positive coefficient of correlation , low standard of error, and high percentage of coefficient of determination. Regression equations determine the relationship between to things, and find out if they are positive or negative, how strong they are, and predicitions with other variables plugged into the same model/equation. It can be used extinsively in business to determine how to invest in different strategies of increasing sales, employee performance, and countless other things.
